    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look toward a heavy slate today, led by **Kyle Tucker** (79.86) and **Andy Pages** (70.96), both of whom benefit significantly from a favorable matchup against Chris Paddack. **Kyle Tucker** stands as our highest-projected asset; despite the pending lineup status, his base projection, combined with a 15% SP skill advantage and beneficial wind conditions, makes him our anchor. **Andy Pages** remains a high-floor start in the heart of the order, capitalizing on the same vulnerable pitching matchup. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (68.69) also demands a start in the 3-hole, where his strong xwOBA of 0.384 and park factors help mitigate the challenge posed by a competent left-handed starter.\n\nOur bench decisions remain tight, with **Nolan Schanuel** (53.20) serving as the most difficult omission. He narrowly missed the cut behind **Miguel Vargas** (53.10), though **Miguel Vargas** carries heightened risk today due to a 38% rain probability and winds blowing in, which eroded his total score despite an elite matchup against a soft Kochanowicz arm. While **Josh Jung** (49.52) also provided respectable output, he was benched in favor of higher-ceiling options against more exploitable pitching. We are monitoring the status of **Liam Hicks** (44.05) closely; while his score is marginal, the dynamic platoon advantage against Yoshinobu Yamamoto keeps him active, provided he secures the number five spot in the order as projected. \n\nBeyond the primary lineup, we are holding firm on the status of **Gunnar Henderson** and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, both of whom are inactive today due to team off-days. We will rely on **Marcell Ozuna** (55.96) to round out our utility slot, relying on his SP skill advantage to offset the negative wind impact at his home park. Investors should remain wary of the rain risk surrounding **Miguel Vargas**, and we continue to evaluate whether to pivot to **Nolan Schanuel** if the weather outlook in that game degrades further.",
